parameters.townshipsMouseover:
Townships Data
Much of rural Ontario is subdivided into geographic townships. These administrative areas are used to organize land surveying and natural resource exploration.
parameters.miningMouseover:
Mining Data
These map layers contain data provided by Ministry of Northern Development and Mines about current claims and abandoned mine sites.
parameters.forestryMouseover:
Forestry Data
These map layers show information about Ontario's Crown forest management units and cut block information.
parameters.communityMouseover:
Community Data
These map layers contain information provided by the community about Culture, Environment, Habitat, Subsistence and Transportation.
parameters.boundaryMouseover:
Boundary Data
These map layers display information about the location of the boundaries between the five different First Nations that make up the Wabun Tribal Council.
parameters.crowdsourceMouseover:
Community Crowdsourced Data
These map layers contain photographs taken by community members in the territory. These present information about Culture, Environment, Habitat, Subsistence and Transportation.

parameters.comments: should be arrays of layer ids indexed by group name
